      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why V Is a Tricky Letter in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>V sits in an awkward spot: it's worth 4 points (respectable), but it has no two-letter words and limited short-word options. Unlike X or Z which can form quick two-letter scores (AX, ZA), V demands at least a three-letter play. This means V can linger on your rack waiting for the right board opening.</p>
      <p>The trick is to play V early before the board closes up. When open lanes exist, V-words score well thanks to the built-in 4-point bonus. But wait too long and you might be stuck trading it in at end-game — a costly penalty.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Playing V-Words</h2>
      <p>Master these approaches to turn V from a liability into a scoring weapon:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Play V early:</strong> Don't hold V hoping for a perfect spot. The board gets tighter each turn. A decent 12-point V-word now beats being stuck with it at end-game.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Combine V with X:</strong> VORTEX, VEXED, VIXEN — when you draw both V and X, these words produce massive scores (15-16 pts base).</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Know your VE- and VI- words:</strong> The most common V-word openings are VE- and VI-. Having 5-6 of each memorised ensures you always have plays available.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Target triple-letter squares:</strong> V on a triple-letter = 12 points for one tile. Combined with a word multiplier, a single V placement can be worth 20+ bonus points.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Beware of end-game V:</strong> If you're stuck with V at the end, you lose 4 points. Plan to play it before the tile bag empties.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Short V-Words for Tight Boards</h2>
